comments.body:
@vrothberg 
I apologize, I forgot to include the following when setting to `journald` mode.
`Error: failed to initialize journal: journald logging only enabled with systemd on linux: no support for this OS yet`
This is on Debian and I am running rootfull for this container.

@rhatdan 
When I run the container just as a `podman run` command in my terminal, as long as I use `-t` I see the entrypoint output and systemd output from the container. However, when I put that command in the unit file, I get no output, either in `podman logs` or on the host journal. I have other containers that I run in a similar way with similar settings that do log to the journal.
